<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=18374></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f18374><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=18374 style='color: darkblue;'>What to kill</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Kellan</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 15th 10:06 AM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There appears to be nothing that makes Grimrot spawn over the PH.  It seems no different from any other mob & PH -- they have a percentage chance on the encounter table as to whether it is Grimrot or the PH.  What does appear to matter is what Norrath time the spot spawns.  This is the only "trigger" per se that seems to be valid.<br><br>A friend has been camping Grimrot all day every day for the past couple weeks, logging in his pally at the spot for the 3 1/2 hour RL spawns (but not at RL night -- silly pally).  He has tried every theory and combination but has yet to get a single Grimrot spawn while there.  I, however, walked up last night and was killing putrids for more faction (after doing the 2gp Lovashun quest 1000 times to get kindly) when my pally friend logs in and says the spot is due in about 1 Norrath hour (12AM nighttime) and he logs back out.  Less than 5 mins RL time up pops dead Grimrot while everything in the camp was alive except one putrid spot.  Two nukes (at 685 damage each) while meleeing and I have a heart.  Camped to go to bed.  Spot is due to respawn at 3PM Norrath time in 3 1/2 RL hours.<br><br>I logged in this morning (about 6 1/2 RL hours later) to see live Grimrot waiting for me.  Everything was alive in the camp, but I cannot be sure what was alive when he spawned.  I buffed and was medding when an Aviak avocet attacked him - good luck for me - and took out 25% of Grimrot's hp.  Although only at 85% mana, I nuked him anyway.  What should have been a 540 DD hit for 52.  Uh oh.  He resisted a total of 5 roots, 3 stuns, and one fear -- NONE landed and I am level 56 -- insane MR on the live Grimrot.  I started straight nukes, which he interrupted over half the time (my channeling is 212) and he took only full damage on one cast.  I now have the scythe.<br><br>Moral to this story is that it seems to be blind luck as to whether you get a PH or a Grimrot - just like virtually all other old-world encounter tables.<br><br>P.S.  Karma is a great thing in the universe.  I spent 10 hours Saturday running the monthly lottery on Cazic and at least 12 hours trying to trade for 51+ spells for my guildmates Sunday / Monday.  Then I walk up to Grimrot and get both pieces in less than 90 minutes total camping time.  What goes around comes around.  Now if the AC is so generous when I go to OOT...<br><br>Kellan<br>Element of Darkness<br>Cazic-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
