	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi All, I have figured this camp out.<br><br>IF you keep all the skellies alive that surround grimrot from one spawn to the next, then grimrot will spawn, either in human of skeleton form.  It is random.  <br>At first I kept killing skellies to keep the camp clear.  Then my friend said that she got it by not clearing it but by just killing the two skellies next to the PH.  Well, once I got that info I made sure that I kept all those skellies alive--shouted, requesting that no one kill any skellie, killed any egrets or darters that threatened the life of one of those skellies, and even p-leveled players who usually hunt the skellies for experience.  Once I did that I was rewarded with 3 Grimrots in a row.  The first two were live and the last one was dead.  The last time I did not kill the two putrids next to the PH just to see what would happen.  I know for a fact, however,  that they are not a trigger.  Neither is the time when you kill the PH.  It is random--you keep the skellies alive and if you are lucky what you need will spawn.<br><br>I camped this with my friend Talidorn--23 cleric--who is one happy camper, so to speak.  We started the camp on Saturday 11AM and finished on Sunday 2:40PM--straight camping--that is right--ugh.  Now we know the secret, so it should only take 9-12 hours to repeat the process with friends.  Kill the place holder when you get there, then keep all the skellies alive until the next pop.  It is as simple as that.  I would guess that there is actually only one or two skellies that NEED to be kept alive (notice how we could kill the two putrids right next to the PH without affecting the spawn), but I will be damned if I am going to spend my time figuring out which one (s) they are.  <br><br>Now, it is all about faction.  Woo hoo, and congrats, Talidorn!!<br><br>Daarkwood Foresst<br>51 Pathfinder, Quellious<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
