<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=14027></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f14027><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/quest.html?quest=454&mid=14027 style='color: darkblue;'>Test Server findings</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Test Cleric</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 27th 12:27 PM</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey folks, I play on the Test Server, and I've been camping this for over a week now, and after talking to a few GM's on Test Server about it possibly being bugged, I can only say the following:<br><br>The PH is no longer supposed to despawn on his own, that's what was supposed to be "fixed" in that patch last week.  If he still does on your server, keep it to yourself, as it will be "fixed" if it's found out.  You MUST kill the PH now to get a chance of one of the two forms of Grimrot to spawn.  Which means plan on a long camp.  The respawn time is between 210 and 220 minutes depending on the system clock on the server you play on, and how fast it ticks off "Norath Minutes".<br><br>Higher up on the post listings, Hamur commented on a way to get either one or the other to spawn...   go with that, it's your best bet.  The hour that the spawn actually spawns is in fact the key to which one will spawn.  If he spawns during "Daylight Hours", you have a chance to get the live version, if it spawns during "Nighttime Hours", you have a chance of getting the dead version.  Remember, there's always a chance of getting a PH.  Keep in mind that in Norath, more of the "hours of the day" count as "night time" then "daytime", so you have fewer hours for the "live version" to spawn in, and thus it is harder to get a live version of Grimrot to spawn.  I plan to do this camp Hamur's way this weekend, when I have time to manipulate the spawns in that fashion.<br><br>If he isn't too regularly camped on your server, you have another option, as a Cleric (sorry, Pallys don't get this option).  Bind at the ruins, and when the servers come back up after going down for any patching, gate there immediately.  There's always a chance one of the two will be up when you get there, lessening the amount of time you have to spend waiting for a spawn.  You can be off leveling somewhere while you wait.  Of course, it will take you a longer time to get it this way, more than likely, but it sure cuts down on the boredom.<br><br>Excellent work Hamur, hope to say it worked for me by next week. :)<br><br>Test Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
